The paper discusses a centrality index in complex networks, specifically in scientific citation networks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the Web of Science, which is a digital library, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses the correlation between network centrality and scientific awards, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC). The use of the $K$-index as a predictor for scientific awards could also be related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-categories.
